cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper discusses the use of image analysis techniques to quantify the geometrical properties of visualized networks in text analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, given the focus on network analysis and text analytics, cs.SI and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The use of image analysis techniques also suggests a potential fit with cs.CV, while the focus on text analysis suggests a potential fit with cs.CL. Finally, the mention of digital libraries in the cs.DL sub-category could also be relevant given the focus on text analysis.
